{"type":"message","id":"9f5d70e8","parentId":"e81d31a5","timestamp":"2026-03-04T02:30:50.055Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9e2d0cc379a24dbca2febc34","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"commit 51a542569536fe16f6673ecfca5aee4cfb6db861\nAuthor: Hendrix <hendrix.ai.dev@gmail.com>\nDate:   Sat Feb 21 11:27:31 2026 -0800\n\n    fix: skip performMaintenance() in dry-run mode\n    \n    performMaintenance() archives session logs and deletes evolver hand\n    sessions regardless of the --dry-run flag. This causes unexpected\n    side effects (moving 1000+ session files) when users expect a\n    read-only dry run.\n    \n    Guard the call with IS_DRY_RUN check so dry-run mode produces no\n    file system mutations.\n\n src/evolve.js | 7 ++++++-\n 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":11,"aggregated":"commit 51a542569536fe16f6673ecfca5aee4cfb6db861\nAuthor: Hendrix <hendrix.ai.dev@gmail.com>\nDate:   Sat Feb 21 11:27:31 2026 -0800\n\n    fix: skip performMaintenance() in dry-run mode\n    \n    performMaintenance() archives session logs and deletes evolver hand\n    sessions regardless of the --dry-run flag. This causes unexpected\n    side effects (moving 1000+ session files) when users expect a\n    read-only dry run.\n    \n    Guard the call with IS_DRY_RUN check so dry-run mode produces no\n    file system mutations.\n\n src/evolve.js | 7 ++++++-\n 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772591450054}}
{"type":"message","id":"b83021ae","parentId":"9f5d70e8","timestamp":"2026-03-04T02:30:50.070Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9fc6ac09e56c4b0d9e2453a1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"commit 882480123ff5c51d1eae9a93003799a303eaab6f\nAuthor: Yewlne <dev@yewlne.com>\nDate:   Fri Feb 20 19:30:29 2026 +0800\n\n    fix: respect gene max_files constraint; remove variable shadowing\n    \n    Two fixes in this commit:\n    \n    1. Gene max_files constraint silently ignored (solidify.js:265)\n       `Math.max(Number(constraints.max_files) || 0, 20)` forced the\n       effective limit to at least 20, so any gene with `max_files < 20`\n       (e.g. the built-in gene at line 780 uses `max_files: 12`) had its\n       constraint silently overridden. Replace with a conditional that only\n       falls back to the default of 20 when no constraint is configured:\n         Number(constraints.max_files) > 0 ? Number(constraints.max_files) : DEFAULT_MAX_FILES\n    \n    2. Redundant variable declarations shadowing outer scope\n       - solidify.js: `const sourceType` re-declared inside the\n         `eligible_to_broadcast` block with identical logic; the outer\n         declaration (line 942) is already in scope there.\n       - evolve.js: `const selectedBy` re-declared inside the solidify\n         `try` block with identical logic; the outer declaration (line 1036)\n         is already in scope there.\n       Removing the inner declarations eliminates the shadowing and ensures\n       any future change to the outer declaration propagates correctly.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n src/evolve.js       | 1 -\n src/gep/solidify.js | 4 ++--\n 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":10,"aggregated":"commit 882480123ff5c51d1eae9a93003799a303eaab6f\nAuthor: Yewlne <dev@yewlne.com>\nDate:   Fri Feb 20 19:30:29 2026 +0800\n\n    fix: respect gene max_files constraint; remove variable shadowing\n    \n    Two fixes in this commit:\n    \n    1. Gene max_files constraint silently ignored (solidify.js:265)\n       `Math.max(Number(constraints.max_files) || 0, 20)` forced the\n       effective limit to at least 20, so any gene with `max_files < 20`\n       (e.g. the built-in gene at line 780 uses `max_files: 12`) had its\n       constraint silently overridden. Replace with a conditional that only\n       falls back to the default of 20 when no constraint is configured:\n         Number(constraints.max_files) > 0 ? Number(constraints.max_files) : DEFAULT_MAX_FILES\n    \n    2. Redundant variable declarations shadowing outer scope\n       - solidify.js: `const sourceType` re-declared inside the\n         `eligible_to_broadcast` block with identical logic; the outer\n         declaration (line 942) is already in scope there.\n       - evolve.js: `const selectedBy` re-declared inside the solidify\n         `try` block with identical logic; the outer declaration (line 1036)\n         is already in scope there.\n       Removing the inner declarations eliminates the shadowing and ensures\n       any future change to the outer declaration propagates correctly.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n src/evolve.js       | 1 -\n src/gep/solidify.js | 4 ++--\n 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772591450067}}
